description: Orion and Lightray must rescue a young Earth boy from the clutches of Tyrus and Tracker...while the resurrection of one of the 'old gods' turns into a startling guest appearance.
name: Gods Never Die

description: The Bloodline Saga Part 6 of 6. In the conclusion of "Bloodline," Orion's finally found what he's been seeking...and with that knowledge may come the ultimate choice.
name: Bloodline
Verão Particular
Os Três Entregadores
Olé, Brasil!

description: Since 1936, he has been thrilling his newspaper audiences world-wide. Again, welcome the comics return of the first costumed adventure hero, The Phantom! The Phantom follows the trail of jewel-thieving pirates into a most dangerous adventure. An old foe comes forth to put every skill The Phantom has to the test. Trapped on a Madman's island, the chance of his survival looks as slim as Satan's smile! He must fight sharks with his hands and feet- he must gain the trust of a beautiful woman- and he must prevail through all of this to an explosive conclusion that will leave you breathless! High-octane adventure by fan-favorite Phantom scribe Ben Raab!

Since 1936, he has been thrilling his newspaper audiences worldwide. Now welcome the comics return of the first costumed adventure hero, The Phantom! Deep in the jungle of Bengalla pirates steal a priceless treasure for a greedy art collector. Meanwhile, in London, Diana Walker and her disturbed friend Naida are kidnapped and locked up tight in a twisted sanitarium. Two menacing crimes for the Phantom to solve! Two evil-strewn paths for the Phantom to walk! And one final, ultra-danger filled conclusion!

volume.name: The Phantom: The Treasures of Bagalla

description: The Saviour, Britain's superhero, appears on a talk show, but what are his true motivations?
The Saviour continues to kill priests, while Jesus begins searching for apostles.
Linda tells her story to Jesus, while the Saviour goes to Live Aid and kills another priest .
Jesus and Linda travel to Glascow. Meanwhile, the Saviour helps overthrow Apartheid in South Africa.
The Saviour completes the Grimoire and reveals the truth about Jesus.
Peter Reid looks for help, while The Saviour continues his master plan.

name: Supergirl

description: George Herriman integrated full, spectacular color into Krazy Kat in June, 1935. The gorgeous evolution continues in our third color volume, which includes the Sunday strips from all of 1939 and 1940. The color format opens the floodgates for a massive amount of spectacular, rare color art from series editor Bill Blackbeard and designer Chris Ware's files. Included are an unpublished Herriman painting from the 1920s and other surprises. Most of these strips in this volume have not seen print since originally running in Hearst newspapers over 70 years ago.

volume.name: Krazy & Ignatz in "A Brick Stuffed With Moom-Bims", The Komplete Kat Komics 1939-1940

description: Last Issue

Living among the safe can make you soft.

The main group continues to flesh out the town. Should they trust them? Should they stay? They make sure to be ready for anything by stealing weapons and arming themselves just incase.

Something is building and what it will be is anyone's guess.
name: Too Far Gone, Pt. 1

description:
It's 1971, and far across the galaxy one truly evil overlord is bent on conquering Radioactive Man's Zenith City. But with a little help from Obrian of the New Guard, and the Whatever People, our beloved bolted hero may have all the help he needs to ward off the dark, apocalyptic machinations of...Backseid! Also, witness the Golden Age of Superheroes when "Radio Man" thwarts the pirating ways of "The Broadcast Buccaneers" as they plunder the airwaves.

As noted in the volume description the issue numbers on the covers of these issues are for spoof purposes. The actual issue number is inside. In this case it is "Radioactive Man v2 issue 9"

This issue is a spoof of Jack Kirby's New Gods series.
name: Obrian and the New Guards!

description: It's 1973, and Radioactive Man goes underground to battle student activists and civil unrest as Rod Runtledge (a.k.a. Fallout Boy) is taken hostage at a nearby university! But has Fallout Boy dropped out, tuned in, grown a social conscience, and joined the cause? Find out in this trippy tribute to the alternative comics of yesteryear!
name: No One Gets Over The Underground!

description: In "The Night of the Undead," something zombie-like is attacking the customers at the Springdale Shopping Mall, and it's up to Scooby and the gang to team up with the Chief of Police and a mall security guy to get to the bottom of things!
name: The Night of the Undead!; Velma's Monsters of the World: Yama-Uba; The Beat of the Bayou Beast; Velma's Monsters of the World: Griffin

description: It's 1966 and the Atomic Avenger must battle his way through would-be assassins, frolicsome beach parties, biker gangs, teen crushes and anti-royalist spies to defend a visiting princess. But the Nuclear Knight and his trusty sidekick, Fallout Boy are about to face the greatest challenge of their crimefighting careers - prom night!
name: From Reinmania With Luv, Baby!; The Uncle From M.A.N.N.!

description: The time is April 1953 and the world's Nuclear Knight has fallen victim to his greatest foe - poor sales. But Morty Mann has a surefire way of saving Bongo from bankruptcy court - combine the most popular comics of the day, horror comics, with the most popular super-hero, Radioactive Man. The result is super-horrific. Featuring the Golden Age stylings of some of comicdom's greatest inkers.
name: The Amazing Radioactive Spider!; The Thing in Head!; The Beauty Queen From The 21st Century!

description: It's January, 1984. Dr. Bix Bentley of the Superior Squad has devised a plan to free Radioactive Man from the lighting bolt imbedded in his brain once and for all. But the best laid plans of Bug Boy and men often go awry, and a new Radioactive Man is born! And believe us when we tell you, this RM is no boy scout! With Zenith in the midst of a media maelstrom over the new Radioactive Man, someone has to put it all back together again... Radioactive Man's alter ego, Claude Kane III! It's a three-part story arc told in one big issue, featuring a special cover by fan favorite, Howard Chaykin!
name: Don't Look Now, But It's 1984!; Eighty-Sixed in '84!; It's 1984... Do You Know Where Your Secret Identity Is?

description: Radioactive Man has gone insane! Why else world he be fighting invisible enemies and causing collateral damage throughout Zenith City? Or perhaps it has something to do, Dr. Claude Kane II's recent invention "Foreverlution," communists run amok, or the return of one of the Atomic Avenger's greatest foes. Be that as it may, this "key" issue in RM's compendium of classic comics has our Man of the Atom battling dinosaurs!
name: The Hallucinations That Weren't Real; Isle of The Irregular Dinosaurs

description: Veronica declares that it's 'Romance Week' and has Jughead deliver the news to Archie in full 'town crier' attire. Can Archie meet Ronnie's exacting demands? Perhaps with some help from Betty! Then, a beach volleyball team is all that stands between Jughead and the ice cream man - and the volleyballers never see Jug coming! Plus, puzzles, games, pin-ups, and more!
name: Decree Degree

description: Radioactive Man's fellow super-heroes, The Superior Squadron, take center stage in their ultra-tech Rumpus Room. Captain Squid stretches his tentacles, Plasmo goes on an inter- dimensional shopping spree, and at long last the true origin of Bug Boy is finally told.
name: Risky Be The Rumpus Room; The Secret Origin of Bug Boy; A Shrimp In Time Pays Fine; The Grotesque Garage Sale of Gargamash!

description:
At last! The story can be told, and the weekend box office receipts can be counted! The film that put the Springfield Tourism and Film Production Office on the map and bankrupted a major Hollywood studio is ready for release and Bongo Comics is pleased to present the long awaited - official movie adaptation! Starring Rainier Wolfcastle as Radioactive Man and introducing Milhouse Van Houten as his trusted sidekick Fallout Boy, this faithful four color rendition of the Nuclear Knight's tragically heroic origin and his fight for fairly-conservative values will have every man, woman, and child in America looking to the skies and exclaiming those famous words, "Up and Atom!"

Chapter Titles

  1. Radioactive Man: The Official Movie Adaption
  2. Radioactive Man, Star of Comics, Stage, Screen, TV, and then some more! (The history of Radioactive Man from 1952 to the present on two pages.)
name: The Official Movie Adaptation

description: Last issue, and the end of Good Comics, Inc.

name: Topolino e il salto del salmone

description: The latest from Freak Brothers creator Gilbert Shelton! The Not Quite Dead, "The World's Least Famous Rock Band," have the opportunity of a lifetime when they're offered an international tour with a high-paying gig in the remote kingdom of Shnagrlig. But they're really being set up by a nefarious secret government agency. Will they survive? A 52-page trade paperback in full color on glossy stock.

name: Topolino e il mistero dell'uccello razzo
